    • Uses of MOStrategy in net.sf.jclec.mo.strategy

      Subclasses of MOStrategy in net.sf.jclec.mo.strategy 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  GrEA
      GrEA strategy The Grid based Evolutionary Algorithm proposes the partition of the objective space into grids, which are adaptively constructed considering the objectives values in the current population.
      class  HypE
      HypE strategy The Hypervolume Estimation Algorithm for Multiobjective Optimization proposes the use of the hypervolume indicator to guide the search toward the Pareto front.
      class  IBEA
      IBEA strategy The Indicator Based Evolutionary Algorithm (IBEA) is a general multiobjective algorithm that allows the user to set the desired quality indicator that will guide the search.
      class  IBEAe
      IBEA implementation using epsilon indicator.
      class  IBEAhv
      IBEA implementation using hypervolume indicator.
      class  MOCHC
      MOCHC strategy This strategy implements the adaptation of CHC algorithm to multi-objective optimization.
      class  MOEAD
      MOEA/D strategy The Multi Objective Evolutionary Algorithm based on Decomposition simultaneously performs an optimization of diverse scalar subproblems.
      class  MOEADte
      MOEA/D strategy with the Tchebycheff approach.
      class  MOEADws
      MOEA/D strategy with the Weigthed Sum approach.
      class  MOPSOStrategy
      Abstract strategy for a multi-objective PSO (MOPSO) algorithm.
      class  NSGA2
      NSGA-II strategy.
      class  NSGA3
      NSGA-III strategy.
      class  OMOPSO
      OMOPSO strategy.
      class  PAES
      PAES strategy.
      class  PAESlambda
      PAES strategy.
      class  PAR
      PAR strategy.
      class  RVEA
      RVEA strategy.
      class  SMPSO
      SMPSO strategy.
      class  SMSEMOA
      SMS-EMOA strategy The S Metric Selection Evolutionary Multi Objective Algorithm is a steady-state algorithm that uses the S metric (hypervolume) to select the individuals that contribute the most to the metric in both the mating selection and environmental selection.
      class  SPEA2
      SPEA2 strategy The Strength Pareto Evolutionary Algorithm 2 (SPEA2) is an algorithm which incorporates a fine-grained fitness assignment strategy, a density estimation technique, and an enhanced archive truncation method.
      class  SSeMOEA
      eMOEA strategy The Steady State epsilon Multi Objective Evolutionary Algorithm is a steady state algorithm that adapts the concept of Pareto dominance.
